From f881d230beb81c142d4be140c4cb041ea46314ed Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 23 Apr 2026 01:15:57 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] T2.2f: Migrate 4 dashboard pages to useQuery
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Fifth slice of the T2.2 react-query fan-out. Migrates the four
dashboard pages (TC, Investor, PML, Admin) from useState+useEffect
+Promise.all(load) to per-entity useQuery calls.

Key design choice: each dashboard uses SEPARATE useQuery calls per
entity (rather than one combined query) so the cache entries share
with other pages using the same queryKey shape. Example: InvestorDashboard's
['Deal', { investor_id: user.id }] is the same shape as what DealBoard
would produce for that investor, so navigation between the two hits
cache.

Page-specific highlights:

- PMLDashboard: 2 queries (MessageThread, PMLProfile). Simplest.

- TCDashboard: 4 queries. Reviews cascade via 'enabled: !!profile?.id'
  after the TCProfile query resolves — mirrors the pattern established
  in T2.2e TCProfilePage.

- InvestorDashboard: 4 queries. Deal + ServiceRequest filtered server-
  side by investor_id. DealApplication is full-list (no Base44 filter
  for 'deal_id IN [...]') and filtered client-side for applicant counts.

- AdminDashboard: 5 queries. Synthetic-application derivation moved
  into useMemo (pure function of apps + users). Mutation handler
  (handleAction) replaced load() with a refreshAfterMutation() helper
  that invalidates ['MemberApplication'] AND ['User'] — approving
  changes a user's role, so other admin views reading the User cache
  must refresh.

MessageThread filtering (threads.filter(t => t.participants?.includes(user.id)))
now lives in a useMemo keyed on allThreads + user.id across all three
dashboards that use it. Consistent with existing pattern in DealBoard.

Mutations NOT converted to useMutation (same rationale as T2.2b, T2.2d):
handleAction has meaningful per-handler logic (email side effects, bundled
toast messaging) that stays clearer as try/catch + await.

Files (4):
- src/pages/dashboard/TCDashboard.jsx       (+37/-20)
- src/pages/dashboard/InvestorDashboard.jsx (+30/-19)
- src/pages/dashboard/PMLDashboard.jsx      (+23/-17)
- src/pages/dashboard/AdminDashboard.jsx    (+64/-39)

Verification:
- npm run lint: 0 errors (full codebase)
- Scoped lint: 0 errors, 4 pre-existing warnings (unused vars)
- npm run build: succeeds
- All useEffect/useCallback/load() removed from dashboards
